   <body>
      <prereq>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <p>The role of the logged-in user should be one of the following:<ul>
                     <li>Administrative Support</li>
                     <li>Construction Inspector</li>
                     <li>Construction Manager</li>
                     <li>Engineer of Record</li>
                     <li>Director</li>
                     <li>Field Supervisor</li>
                     <li>Fund Manager</li>
                     <li>Manager</li>
                     <li>Program Manager</li>
                     <li>Project Manager</li>
                     <li>Support Services</li>
                  </ul>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context>You can create a portfolio to group the projects, programs, and sub-portfolios. For ease of tracking, you can create portfolios that are in the purview of a user, and assign projects, programs, and sub-portfolios.</context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click<uicontrol>Home</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>ENTERPRISE DASHBOARD</uicontrol>page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, click<uicontrol>Portfolio</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>PORTFOLIO</uicontrol> list page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click<uicontrol>New</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>
               <fig product="PG_Screenshot">
                  <title>Portfolio Page</title>
                  <image href="../../../Icons/Portfolio.jpg" placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>PORTFOLIO</uicontrol> page  displays the following non-editable  fields:<table colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="30%"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="70%"/>
                     <thead>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Field Name</entry>
                           <entry>Description</entry>
                        </row>
                     </thead>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Created By</entry>
                           <entry>Displays the name of the user creating the portfolio.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Created Date</entry>
                           <entry>The current date is displayed.</entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the<uicontrol>DETAILS</uicontrol> tab, provide the required information in the fields, as described in the following table.</p>
            <p>
               <table colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="30%"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="70%"/>
                     <thead>
                        <row>
                           <entry>Field Name</entry>
                           <entry>Description</entry>
                        </row>
                     </thead>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry> Portfolio Name </entry>
                           <entry>Enter a unique name for the portfolio.
                                    </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry> Portfolio Manager </entry>
                           <entry>To select the portfolio manager, perform the following steps: 
                                        <ol>
                                 <li>Click <image href="../../../Icons/select.png" placement="inline">
                                       <alt>List</alt>
                                    </image>. <p>The <uicontrol>Portfolio Managers </uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</p> The list comprises user names of all users in the enterprise.
                                            </li>
                                 <li>Select the required portfolio manager, and then click <uicontrol>Select</uicontrol>.</li>
                              </ol>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry> Description </entry>
                           <entry>Enter a detailed description of the portfolio.
 </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry> Start Date </entry>
                           <entry>Select the start date of the portfolio.
                                    </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry> End Date </entry>
                           <entry>Select the end date of the portfolio.
                                    </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To add projects to the portfolio, in the <uicontrol>PROJECTS</uicontrol> section, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Click<uicontrol>Add</uicontrol>.</p>
                  <p>The<uicontrol>Projects</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.<p>The list of all the projects in the enterprise is displayed.</p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select the required projects, and then click<uicontrol>Select</uicontrol>.</p>
                  <p>The selected projects are added to the portfolio.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To add programs to the portfolio, in the <uicontrol>PROGRAMS</uicontrol> section, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Click<uicontrol>Add</uicontrol>.</p>
                  <p>The<uicontrol>Programs</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.<p>The list of all the programs in the enterprise is displayed.</p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select the required programs, and then click<uicontrol>Select</uicontrol>.</p>
                  <p>The selected programs are added to the portfolio.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>To add portfolios as sub-portfolios, in the <uicontrol>SUB PORTFOLIOS</uicontrol> section, perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>Click<uicontrol>Add</uicontrol>.</p>
                  <p>The<uicontrol>Sub Portfolios</uicontrol>dialog box is displayed.<p>The list of all the portfolios in the enterprise is displayed.</p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select the required portfolios, and then click<uicontrol>Select</uicontrol>.</p>
                  <p>The selected portfolios are added as sub-portfolios to the portfolio.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Save</uicontrol> to save the record and return to the list page.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
